it's been nice meeting you.

467
00:41:01,528 --> 00:41:04,836
I hope the rest of the trip for both
of us is a little less exhilarating.

468
00:41:04,836 --> 00:41:06,705
Let's hope so.

469
00:41:08,378 --> 00:41:12,508
Well, I think I've made a silly fool
of myself this morning.

470
00:41:12,508 --> 00:41:14,242
- No, no, not at all.
- No, no, I did.

471
00:41:14,242 --> 00:41:19,049
I was just sticking my nose into a lot
of stuff that's none of my business..

472
00:41:19,049 --> 00:41:22,249
and coming up with some crazy ideas.
You were right.

473
00:41:23,359 --> 00:41:26,294
I guess I was imagining
a lot of things last night.

474
00:41:27,463 --> 00:41:28,953
Probably the champagne.

475
00:41:32,668 --> 00:41:35,694
- Well
- Let me clean your jacket..

476
00:41:35,694 --> 00:41:38,467
Oh, that's all right.
I have another one.

477
00:41:38,467 --> 00:41:41,942
We get to Chicago tomorrow and
I did come on this trip to do some work.

478
00:41:41,942 --> 00:41:43,706
So I'll say good-bye.

479
00:41:43,706 --> 00:41:47,306
- Couldn't you possibly join us for dinner?
- Oh, yes, do.

480
00:41:48,584 --> 00:41:51,143
Thanks. No.
I think I'll just eat in my room.

481
00:41:58,526 --> 00:42:01,393
This latch...
seems to be stuck.

482
00:42:03,298 --> 00:42:05,823
I'll get the porter
to fix it right away.

483
00:42:37,130 --> 00:42:39,894
What are you up to there, lover boy?

484
00:42:39,894 --> 00:42:41,958
Hello, Bob Sweet.

485
00:42:42,636 --> 00:42:44,627
- Hello, Bobby.
- How are ya?

486
00:42:46,006 --> 00:42:47,234
I'm all right.

487
00:42:47,234 --> 00:42:51,209
Better yet, uh, what are you?
A miniature alcoholic?

488
00:42:51,209 --> 00:42:54,509
Did you know that
the Blanard Tunnel...

489
00:42:54,509 --> 00:42:57,049
was the highest point on this line?

490
00:42:57,049 --> 00:42:58,413
Yeah, I knew that.

491
00:42:58,413 --> 00:43:01,647
Did you know that when we reach it,
I intend to be higher?

492
00:43:02,521 --> 00:43:05,319
- Just don't fall off, huh? Okay?
- Oh, no.

493
00:43:05,319 --> 00:43:08,986
I've left this train once already.
That's enough.

494
00:43:08,986 --> 00:43:11,689
You have? What do you mean?

495
00:43:11,689 --> 00:43:14,062
Last night...

496
00:43:14,062 --> 00:43:16,727
just as I was about to...

497
00:43:17,837 --> 00:43:20,499
kiss my beautiful blonde...

498
00:43:20,499 --> 00:43:23,838
I saw her boss
hanging outside the window.

499
00:43:23,838 --> 00:43:26,173
Wait. You saw her boss,
Professor Schreiner, huh?

500
00:43:26,173 --> 00:43:27,974
That's him.

501
00:43:27,974 --> 00:43:29,947
That's the fellow.

502
00:43:29,947 --> 00:43:32,041
He was shot in the head.

503
00:43:33,685 --> 00:43:36,176
I knew that
I had been drinking...

504
00:43:36,176 --> 00:43:38,916
so I went to see
the professor this morning...

505
00:43:38,916 --> 00:43:41,754
and I found this
little weasel of a guy in his room.

506
00:43:41,754 --> 00:43:44,158
- Edgar Whiney.
- That's him.

507
00:43:44,158 --> 00:43:47,687
- How did you know that?
- Oh, I-I know. I just know.

508
00:43:47,687 --> 00:43:49,757
Go on, go on.

509
00:43:49,757 --> 00:43:52,564
Well, then this huge mountain...

510
00:43:52,564 --> 00:43:55,367
with a gold mine stuck in his gums...

511
00:43:55,367 --> 00:43:59,501
picked me up and
threw me off the train.

512
00:43:59,501 --> 00:44:03,013
- What... But you never saw the professor, huh?
- No, I saw him.

513
00:44:03,013 --> 00:44:05,379
- I saw him this afternoon.
- Where?

514
00:44:05,379 --> 00:44:07,384
In Hilly's compartment.

515
00:44:07,384 --> 00:44:11,285
See, the man I saw last night
was a hallucination.

516
00:44:12,222 --> 00:44:14,713
- What did he look like?
- Who?

517
00:44:14,713 --> 00:44:17,226
The professor, you know,
that you saw this afternoon.

518
00:44:17,226 --> 00:44:19,387
Like his picture.

519
00:44:19,387 --> 00:44:24,127
- Did he say anything to you?
- Why are you asking me all these questions?

520
00:44:24,127 --> 00:44:26,692
- Did he say anything...
- Nothing, nothing.

521
00:44:26,692 --> 00:44:28,897
He was tired
and wanted to have a scotch.

522
00:44:29,807 --> 00:44:33,174
You don't have any ice in your drink.
- That's it! Scotch!

523
00:44:34,244 --> 00:44:37,236
Listen. See, you didn't have
a hallucination.

524
00:44:38,248 --> 00:44:40,216
The professor's been murdered.

525
00:44:40,216 --> 00:44:43,081
The guy you saw this afternoon
was a fake.

526
00:44:43,081 --> 00:44:44,881
Oh, no.

527
00:44:44,881 --> 00:44:49,084
Yeah. Listen, I talked to the real
professor last night. I mean it.

528
00:44:49,084 --> 00:44:51,854
He didn't wanna have anything
to do with Mr. Devereau.

529
00:44:51,854 --> 00:44:54,658
Besides that, he's a health nut.
Doesn't touch alcohol.

530
00:44:54,658 --> 00:44:58,360
Oh, Bobby, just because
you're a vitamin salesman?

531
00:44:58,360 --> 00:45:01,096
My name is Stevens.
I'm a federal agent.

532
00:45:04,240 --> 00:45:07,073
We've been working on this case
for two and a half years.

533
00:45:08,044 --> 00:45:10,137
Well, what are you tailing
the professor for?

534
00:45:10,137 --> 00:45:13,273
I am not tailing the professor,
I'm tailing Devereau.

535
00:45:13,273 --> 00:45:14,611
Come on. Let's go.

536
00:45:14,611 --> 00:45:17,174
Wait a minute. What about Hilly?

537
00:45:17,174 --> 00:45:20,153
Don't worry about it. They're not
gonna kill her till we get to Chicago.

538
00:45:20,153 --> 00:45:22,918
I don't even think they'll try
to kill you till then. Come on.

539
00:45:25,527 --> 00:45:28,121
Devereau's men must've brought the
professor back here...

540
00:45:28,121 --> 00:45:30,027
after 9:00 pm last night.

541
00:45:30,027 --> 00:45:33,829
- How do you figure that?
- Because I left him at 9:00 pm.

542
00:45:33,829 --> 00:45:38,362
And because this is the easiest access
to the roof. Somehow, he must've escaped.

543
00:45:38,362 --> 00:45:41,967
He got out to this ladder, then ran back
down the train before they shot him.

544
00:45:45,647 --> 00:45:48,343
You're not going up there, are you?

545
00:45:48,343 --> 00:45:51,976
Yeah. The Blanard Tunnel is up ahead.

546
00:45:51,976 --> 00:45:54,714
Come on up and
keep a lookout, will ya?

547
00:45:54,714 --> 00:45:56,848
All right, I'll try.

548
00:46:37,029 --> 00:46:39,088
What did you find?

549
00:46:39,088 --> 00:46:41,098
It was hooked on
a protruding bolt.

550
00:46:44,102 --> 00:46:47,333
Then I was right.
I did see him.

551
00:46:59,785 --> 00:47:05,017
I'll bet Devereau has already got the body
picked up and placed in cold storage someplace.

552
00:47:06,090 --> 00:47:08,888
Too bad.
He was a sweet old guy.

553
00:47:08,888 --> 00:47:11,689
Buy why did he have
to kill the professor?

554
00:47:11,689 --> 00:47:15,630
He was going to be embarrassed
by the findings in the professor's book.

555
00:47:17,001 --> 00:47:19,060
Two of the institute's Rembrandts...

556
00:47:19,060 --> 00:47:22,003
both bought and authenticated
by Devereau...

557
00:47:22,003 --> 00:47:24,166
were going to be proved forgeries.

558
00:47:25,242 --> 00:47:28,439
The professor had the proof
in his possession.

559
00:47:29,547 --> 00:47:31,879
I asked him last night,
"What was the proof?"

560
00:47:32,817 --> 00:47:36,718
He told me I was going
to have to wait for his lecture.

561
00:47:36,718 --> 00:47:38,777
And Devereau wasn't going to wait.

562
00:47:41,124 --> 00:47:44,560
I think the idea
was to kidnap the professor...

563
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:46,618
then kill him...

564
00:47:46,618 --> 00:47:50,063
and then substitute
some phony look-alike...

565
00:47:50,063 --> 00:47:52,863
who would botch the lecture
and discredit the book.

566
00:47:54,337 --> 00:47:57,795
- We've gotta find the proof.
- But they have the proof.

567
00:47:57,795 --> 00:48:00,707
They have it. That's what Whiney
and everyone was looking for this morning...

568
00:48:00,707 --> 00:48:02,244
the Rembrandt letters.

569
00:48:02,244 --> 00:48:05,873
They said that they found them
in the professor's trunk.

570
00:48:05,873 --> 00:48:08,918
They're lying. That's the first place
they would've looked...

571
00:48:08,918 --> 00:48:12,385
before they started turning
his room upside down.

572
00:48:13,722 --> 00:48:16,782
No! No, the professor hid them
someplace, somewhere simple...

573
00:48:16,782 --> 00:48:20,056
as a precaution when he found out
Devereau was on the train.

574
00:48:20,056 --> 00:48:22,689
My God! I know where they are!
Come on! Come on!

575
00:48:46,788 --> 00:48:48,779
The Rembrandt letters.

576
00:48:51,058 --> 00:48:53,720
Holy Toledo!
I think you've found it.

577
00:48:55,763 --> 00:48:58,823
This is the genuine article,
penned by the old boy himself, huh?

578
00:48:58,823 --> 00:49:02,495
"Rembrandt Harmenszoon Van Rijn. "

579
00:49:03,971 --> 00:49:06,963
Yeah. My guess is there's a fact there's
some kind of a date in all this...

580
00:49:06,963 --> 00:49:09,771
that proves the charges the professor
makes in his book.

581
00:49:09,771 --> 00:49:13,280
Push the button for the porter, will ya?
I wanna get the conductor to radio ahead
to the next town.

582
00:49:13,280 --> 00:49:18,307
You know, it's difficult to believe
that a man was killed over those.

583
00:49:18,307 --> 00:49:21,218
This is the tip of an iceberg.

584
00:49:21,218 --> 00:49:23,779
You know that plane crash
in Cologne, Germany last year?

585
00:49:23,779 --> 00:49:27,793
That was a Devereau special.
A hundred people got killed in that one.

586
00:49:27,793 --> 00:49:31,695
It was just to cover up his involvement
in the Metropolitan Gallery scandal.

587
00:49:31,695 --> 00:49:34,427
We knew he was responsible.
We couldn't pin it on him.

588
00:49:35,235 --> 00:49:40,468
These letters are gonna blow his
multimillion-dollar operation in art sky-high.

589
00:49:40,468 --> 00:49:44,601
That's why she was so distant.
They must've had her in a corner.

590
00:49:45,412 --> 00:49:47,676
I want you to remember
that your neck is on the line too.

591
00:49:47,676 --> 00:49:49,908
You already told him you saw
the real professor shot.

592
00:49:49,908 --> 00:49:54,010
Yeah, I did.
So what do I do now?

593
00:49:54,010 --> 00:49:56,987
You be responsible for Hilly.
Get her off the train and to safety.

594
00:49:56,987 --> 00:49:59,081
- I'm gonna take care of Mr. Devereau.
- Here comes the tunnel.

595
00:49:59,081 --> 00:50:02,059
We'll make our move when the
train gets to Dodge City tonight.

596
00:50:03,162 --> 00:50:06,154
That's appropriate, huh?
Gun smoke at the O.K. Corral.

597
00:50:13,272 --> 00:50:14,933
What happened?

598
00:50:16,842 --> 00:50:18,707
Bob, what happened?

599
00:50:20,012 --> 00:50:22,071
Put-Put 'em back.

600
00:50:22,071 --> 00:50:25,776
Go on, now. Do it.
Get my gun. Take my gun.

601
00:50:25,776 --> 00:50:29,286
Take my gun. Go on.
Get the girl off the train, okay?

602
00:50:30,288 --> 00:50:31,949
Go on.!

603
00:50:33,858 --> 00:50:36,986
You know, I got a funny feeling
this bullet was meant for you.

604
00:50:42,901 --> 00:50:45,131
Shoot.! That man's dead.!

605
00:50:47,071 --> 00:50:50,438
- Holy moly, you shot him!
- I didn't... No.

606
00:50:51,175 --> 00:50:54,374
- No! Wait a minute!
- He's been shot!

607
00:50:55,980 --> 00:50:57,345
A man's been shot!

608
00:50:58,116 --> 00:51:00,107
I didn't shoot him!

609
00:51:03,854 --> 00:51:05,515
Hey. Hey, you're not...

610
00:51:05,515 --> 00:51:08,683
Hey! He's not dead!

611
00:53:56,722 --> 00:53:58,951
Hold it!
Don't move, or I'll shoot!

612
00:54:38,095 --> 00:54:40,086
Son of a bitch!

613
00:55:23,606 --> 00:55:26,473
Wait! Wait!

614
00:55:31,748 --> 00:55:33,340
Wait!

615
00:55:36,686 --> 00:55:40,213
Wait! Hello!

616
00:55:44,126 --> 00:55:47,584
Hello! Hello, please!
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!

617
00:55:47,584 --> 00:55:50,757
Wait a...
Come on, please! Stop!

618
00:56:03,512 --> 00:56:05,173
Thanks a lot, Eddie.

619
00:56:07,616 --> 00:56:11,245


620
00:56:17,458 --> 00:56:19,426
That's it, boys.!

621
00:56:19,426 --> 00:56:22,088
Blow those babies'heads off!

622
00:56:29,137 --> 00:56:31,071
Excuse me.

623
00:56:31,071 --> 00:56:32,800
Just a minute.

624
00:56:32,905 --> 00:56:35,006
Geez, would you look at that!

625
00:56:38,613 --> 00:56:41,208
That boy is somethin', ain't he?

626
00:56:48,723 --> 00:56:50,247
Commercial.

627
00:56:54,695 --> 00:56:58,187
- Now, what can I do for you?
- I want to report a murder.

628
00:56:58,187 --> 00:57:01,098
A murder. A man's been shot
on the Silver Streak...

629
00:57:01,098 --> 00:57:04,865
and there's a girl who's in great danger.
We have to stop the train.

630
00:57:04,865 --> 00:57:07,270
Now, wait a second.
You say a man's been shot?

631
00:57:08,175 --> 00:57:10,439
- Yes.
- Jumpin'Jiminy!

632
00:57:10,439 --> 00:57:12,706
We've never had a murder before.

633
00:57:12,706 --> 00:57:15,578
Sit down.
Have a cup of coffee. Help yourself.

634
00:57:15,578 --> 00:57:18,311
Now, uh, let's get the facts.

635
00:57:20,420 --> 00:57:24,914
- What did you say your name was?
- Caldwell. George Caldwell.

636
00:57:24,914 --> 00:57:27,619
I'm from Los Angeles.

637
00:57:27,619 --> 00:57:31,789
L.A. Okay.
Who was shot?

638
00:57:31,789 --> 00:57:33,923
- Actually, there were two.
- Two?

639
00:57:33,923 --> 00:57:36,525
Yes. The first was Bob Sweet.

640
00:57:36,525 --> 00:57:38,661
He was a federal undercover agent.

641
00:57:38,661 --> 00:57:40,228
- A fed? No shit?
- Yes.

642
00:57:40,228 --> 00:57:43,537
And the second was a man
by the name of Reace. I shot him.

643
00:57:45,044 --> 00:57:47,706
- You shot him?
- Yes. He shot Sweet.

644
00:57:47,706 --> 00:57:50,180
- Because Sweet was a fed?
- No, because he thought Sweet was me.

645
00:57:50,180 --> 00:57:53,275
- Reace shot Sweet, and you shot Reace?
- Right.

646
00:57:53,275 --> 00:57:56,719
- With a spear gun.
- W-With a what?

647
00:57:56,719 --> 00:57:59,656
You see, I took Sweet's gun,
but I dropped it...

648
00:57:59,656 --> 00:58:01,749
so I had to use a spear gun.

649
00:58:03,261 --> 00:58:05,525
Uh, don't you...
can't we call someone?

650
00:58:05,525 --> 00:58:07,497
Wait a second.
You say you shot Reace with a spear?

651
00:58:07,497 --> 00:58:10,898
Yes. He was going to shoot me.
- With a spear?

652
00:58:10,898 --> 00:58:13,335
No, with a bullet!
He shot the professor.

653
00:58:13,335 --> 00:58:15,498
- Who shot the professor?
- Reace.

654
00:58:15,498 --> 00:58:17,734
- Reace shot Sweet!
- And the professor.

655
00:58:19,344 --> 00:58:21,073
Makes three.

656
00:58:22,380 --> 00:58:26,840
Oh, I'm sorry, I forgot.
The professor was shot last night.

657
00:58:28,953 --> 00:58:31,945
- Uh, can't wejust do all of this later?
- Was there anyone else?

658
00:58:31,945 --> 00:58:34,355
- Anyone else what?
- Shot!

659
00:58:34,355 --> 00:58:38,521
No. No, but there will be soon
if we don't stop the train.

660
00:58:38,521 --> 00:58:42,861
Please, just pick up the phone
and call your superiors.

661
00:58:42,861 --> 00:58:45,458
Tell them I have
the Rembrandt letters.

662
00:58:45,458 --> 00:58:48,801
- That's why the professor was shot.
- Was he with the feds?

663
00:58:48,801 --> 00:58:51,932
- Who?
- This guy Rembrandt.

664
00:58:53,811 --> 00:58:57,645
- Rembrandt is dead.
- Dead? That makes four.

665
00:58:58,549 --> 00:59:01,814
Listen, feller, you sure you're not
makin'this up as you go along?

666
00:59:01,814 --> 00:59:05,286
I'm an officer of the law and I got better
things to do than listen to that funnin'.

667
00:59:07,491 --> 00:59:09,424
That's my hot line.

668
00:59:09,424 --> 00:59:11,551
Now, you take the time to get your facts straight.
When I come back,

669
00:59:11,551 --> 00:59:15,324
I want your answers clear and to the point.
Got that?

670
00:59:15,324 --> 00:59:17,662
And you can start
with who shot Rembrandt.

671
00:59:19,702 --> 00:59:21,795
Hello. Yeah.

672
00:59:22,872 --> 00:59:24,863
This is Chauncey.

673
00:59:26,642 --> 00:59:28,303
No shit!

674
00:59:30,079 --> 00:59:33,480
Jumpin'Jiminy! He's sittin'
right here in my office.

675
00:59:34,884 --> 00:59:36,010
That's right.

676
00:59:36,010 --> 00:59:40,317
Came in here spoutin'some bull about shootin'
some people on the train, wanted to confess.

677
00:59:40,317 --> 00:59:43,290
I knew he was a loony right off.

678
00:59:43,290 --> 00:59:46,020
Oh, yeah. Don't you worry.

679
00:59:46,020 --> 00:59:49,655
I've handled loonies before.
Gotcha.

680
01:00:09,217 --> 01:00:12,050
Sheriff, I'm sorry.
I guess I was a little rattled before.

681
01:00:12,050 --> 01:00:16,489
- It must've sounded crazy to you.
- Oh, that's perfectly all right, Mr. Caldwell.

682
01:00:16,489 --> 01:00:19,287
That is what you said your name was,
didn't you? George Caldwell?

683
01:00:19,287 --> 01:00:20,987
Yeah.

684
01:00:20,987 --> 01:00:23,427
I really think that we oughta
get on the phone to Washington.

685
01:00:23,427 --> 01:00:27,058
If they heard what I have to say,
they would stop the train.

686
01:00:27,058 --> 01:00:29,762
Oh, yeah. Them boys in Washington,
they're pretty smart.

687
01:00:29,762 --> 01:00:32,101
You ever watch 'em on TV? Bam, bam.

688
01:00:32,101 --> 01:00:35,836
Sheriff, listen to me! They know
all about Sweet and Devereau.

689
01:00:35,836 --> 01:00:39,038
I figured that the Silver Streak
should be in Kansas in an hour.

690
01:00:39,038 --> 01:00:41,513
We could stop the train
at Scott City or maybe Dodge.

691
01:00:41,513 --> 01:00:46,246
All right, mister! Keep your hands where
they are, and we'll have no trouble!

692
01:00:47,321 --> 01:00:48,811
- Give me that!
- Don't shoot.

693
01:00:49,456 --> 01:00:51,253
"Don't shoot"?

694
01:00:51,253 --> 01:00:55,226
You stupid, ignorant,
son-of-a-bitch, dumb bastard!

695
01:00:55,226 --> 01:00:59,129
Jesus Christ! I've met some dumb bastards
in my time, but you outdo them all!

696
01:00:59,129 --> 01:01:01,895
Get over there! What the hell
do you think I'm doing?

