921
01:18:06,663 --> 01:18:08,324
Give me the gun.

922
01:18:10,500 --> 01:18:12,491
Now give me your wallet.

923
01:18:13,470 --> 01:18:15,733
- What the...
- I gotta get a disguise... a porter's uniform.

924
01:18:15,733 --> 01:18:19,400
You know, these disguises
are getting expensive.

925
01:18:19,400 --> 01:18:21,705
Crime costs.
Where's it at?

926
01:18:21,705 --> 01:18:25,440
Four cars back, room "C."
Stay out of trouble.

927
01:19:29,643 --> 01:19:32,806
- Hilly, are you all right?
- George, watch it.! Don't come in here.

928
01:20:02,074 --> 01:20:03,939
Are you all right?

929
01:20:03,939 --> 01:20:08,504
That's what I was gonna ask you.
I'm sorry about your head.

930
01:20:08,504 --> 01:20:12,483
I never would have gone back to the
compartment if I thought that you were gonna...

931
01:20:12,483 --> 01:20:14,986
- The Rembrandt letters.
- Devereau's got them.

932
01:20:14,986 --> 01:20:17,181
He found them in your jacket.

933
01:20:18,424 --> 01:20:22,485
- I guess I blew it.
- Poor George.

934
01:20:22,485 --> 01:20:24,996
I tried not to get you involved,...

935
01:20:24,996 --> 01:20:28,522
but they came to me yesterday and they told me
that they'd killed the professor...

936
01:20:28,522 --> 01:20:30,831
and that unless I cooperated,
they'd kill me too.

937
01:20:30,831 --> 01:20:32,802
I thought that...

938
01:20:32,802 --> 01:20:35,772
I'd go along with them
and that then you'd get away.

939
01:20:35,772 --> 01:20:40,540
I was really happy when you did,
but I was afraid I'd never see you again.

940
01:20:47,185 --> 01:20:49,016
George, I was so frightened.

941
01:20:50,489 --> 01:20:52,787
So was I.

942
01:20:52,787 --> 01:20:54,951
I was scared you wouldn't be here.

943
01:20:56,895 --> 01:20:58,192
I missed you, Hilly.

944
01:20:59,631 --> 01:21:01,622
You did?

945
01:21:01,622 --> 01:21:03,691
I missed you too.

946
01:21:11,242 --> 01:21:13,710
You've got shoe polish
behind your ear.

947
01:21:18,849 --> 01:21:21,784
I'll explain that to you later.

948
01:21:21,784 --> 01:21:25,788
- Where are we?
- Just passing the Illinois River Canal.

949
01:21:25,788 --> 01:21:29,155
Well, how are you?
I hope I didn't slug you too hard.

950
01:21:29,155 --> 01:21:32,218
- Where's Devereau?
- Isn't that perfect?

951
01:21:32,218 --> 01:21:36,357
You want to see him,
and he wants to see you.

952
01:21:36,357 --> 01:21:38,765
Ladies first, hmm?

953
01:21:41,138 --> 01:21:42,627
Come in.

954
01:21:45,675 --> 01:21:48,405
Uh, please sit down.
Make yourself comfortable.

955
01:21:48,405 --> 01:21:50,605
Miss Burns, how are you?

956
01:21:50,605 --> 01:21:55,049
Bring us some fresh coffee, toast
and marmalade for our guests, would you?

957
01:21:55,049 --> 01:21:57,109
- Yes, sir.
- Right away.

958
01:22:01,224 --> 01:22:05,217
I'vejust been looking over
this correspondence you brought me...

959
01:22:05,217 --> 01:22:06,217
And...

960
01:22:07,297 --> 01:22:08,992
uh, it's fascinating.

961
01:22:08,992 --> 01:22:11,590
The professor was right.
It's a remarkable find.

962
01:22:11,590 --> 01:22:14,102
I'm almost tempted
to destroy it...

963
01:22:14,102 --> 01:22:18,663
but then on the other hand, I've always
had a soft spot for things of beauty.

964
01:22:18,663 --> 01:22:21,937
Particularly when they were genuine.

965
01:22:21,937 --> 01:22:23,671
Whiney, would you put these
in my safe, please?

966
01:22:23,671 --> 01:22:26,213
I don't think they propose...

967
01:22:26,213 --> 01:22:28,408
any further threat. Do you?

968
01:22:35,891 --> 01:22:38,291
I hope you're not too disappointed
if this doesn't work.

969
01:22:38,291 --> 01:22:40,328
Oh, but on the contrary,
I think it will.

970
01:22:40,328 --> 01:22:43,922
This has been a very difficult project,
and I have made an error or two.

971
01:22:43,922 --> 01:22:48,231
One of them was bringing that man
Reace out here. What happened to him?

972
01:22:48,231 --> 01:22:50,328
I shot him.

973
01:22:50,328 --> 01:22:53,168
Good for you.
He probably deserved it.

974
01:22:53,168 --> 01:22:55,640
You did have him kill
the professor, didn't you?

975
01:22:55,640 --> 01:22:58,178
Oh, no. Oh, no.
On the contrary.

976
01:22:58,178 --> 01:23:01,408
He did that on his own.
An unfortunate mistake.

977
01:23:01,408 --> 01:23:05,612
I knew we couldn't kill the professor
until we had the Rembrandt letters.

978
01:23:05,612 --> 01:23:11,318
So I had to set up a scenario whereby
the, uh, professor was kidnapped...

979
01:23:11,318 --> 01:23:15,590
and an imposter impersonated him
in order to discredit him.

980
01:23:15,590 --> 01:23:18,791
We would have killed him anyway, but
his escape attempt the other night...

981
01:23:18,791 --> 01:23:20,493
upset the entire scheme.

982
01:23:20,493 --> 01:23:22,399
Come in.

983
01:23:23,471 --> 01:23:25,995
Excuse me, sir.
It's all confirmed.

984
01:23:25,995 --> 01:23:28,734
- The car will be waiting at Rockdale.
- Good.

985
01:23:28,734 --> 01:23:31,402
Oh, Mr. Caldwell,
you do rememberJohnson?

986
01:23:31,402 --> 01:23:34,072
He played the part
of the professor...

987
01:23:34,072 --> 01:23:38,208
and would have done the same thing
at Chicago, had it been necessary.

988
01:23:38,918 --> 01:23:41,478
How long before
we arrive at Rockdale?

989
01:23:41,478 --> 01:23:43,988
- About an hour and a half, sir.
- Thank you, Johnson.

990
01:23:44,958 --> 01:23:47,825
Now all that remains
is to clear up a couple of points.

991
01:23:49,029 --> 01:23:50,690
Meaning the two of you.

992
01:23:50,690 --> 01:23:52,857
So I've arranged a new scenario...

993
01:23:52,857 --> 01:23:55,992
wherein you are responsible
for the murder of the professor.

994
01:23:55,992 --> 01:23:59,732
- Why would I kill the professor?
- To get the Rembrandt letters.

995
01:23:59,732 --> 01:24:03,241
He found out and you had to shoot him
because he tried to blackmail you.

996
01:24:03,241 --> 01:24:06,471
Which brings us
more or less up to date...

997
01:24:06,471 --> 01:24:10,037
Except that
in about 45 minutes from now...

998
01:24:10,037 --> 01:24:11,878
the professor's trusty secretary
is going to quarrel...

999
01:24:11,878 --> 01:24:15,784
with her partner/lover...

1000
01:24:15,784 --> 01:24:19,187
and shoot him. And he dies...

1001
01:24:19,187 --> 01:24:22,386
but not before shooting her.

1002
01:24:26,832 --> 01:24:30,563
Ah, enough of this talk
of plots and scenarios.

1003
01:24:30,563 --> 01:24:33,230
Uh, join me in a cup
of coffee, would you?

1004
01:24:34,106 --> 01:24:35,697
Coffee, mister?

1005
01:24:40,611 --> 01:24:43,876
- Thanks.
- The professor's book
is still gonna be published.

1006
01:24:43,876 --> 01:24:46,815
Oh, yes, indeed, my dear.
But without the letters...

1007
01:24:46,815 --> 01:24:50,911
I'm afraid it will be regarded
as the jottings of a revisionist crank.

1008
01:24:50,911 --> 01:24:52,819
An ex-crank,
as a matter of fact.

1009
01:24:52,819 --> 01:24:56,587
The Silver Streak does have its drawbacks,
but please try the marmalade.

1010
01:24:56,587 --> 01:24:59,357
- They do provide an excellent cuisine.
- Oh, thank you, sir.

1011
01:24:59,357 --> 01:25:01,955
I'll tell the boys in the kitchen.
We aims to please.

1012
01:25:01,955 --> 01:25:03,762
- Coffee, miss?
- No, thanks.

1013
01:25:03,762 --> 01:25:07,293
- He ain't bullshittin' about the cuisine.
- Steward?

1014
01:25:07,293 --> 01:25:10,498
- Is that your lady, man? She's somethin' else.
- Steward!

1015
01:25:10,498 --> 01:25:13,634
- Stand up, mama. Let me get a look at you.
- Steward!

1016
01:25:13,634 --> 01:25:16,975
- Mm, mm, mm! Have mercy!
- Steward, you may go. Thank you very much.

1017
01:25:16,975 --> 01:25:19,777
- Just a little more coffee?
- No, thank you.

1018
01:25:19,777 --> 01:25:21,750
Half a cup?
Oh, sorry, sir.

1019
01:25:21,750 --> 01:25:24,946
- Look what I've done.
- You... Get out of...

1020
01:25:24,946 --> 01:25:27,182
- See what I've done...
- You ignorant nigger!

1021
01:25:27,182 --> 01:25:29,191
Who you callin' nigger, huh?

1022
01:25:29,191 --> 01:25:31,352
You don't know me well enough
to call me no nigger!

1023
01:25:31,352 --> 01:25:33,726
I'll slap the taste out your mouth!
You don't even know my name!

1024
01:25:33,726 --> 01:25:35,958
I'll whoop your ass! Beat the white
of your ass.

1025
01:25:35,958 --> 01:25:38,193
- Who are you?
- I'm a thief.

1026
01:25:39,503 --> 01:25:42,768
It's all right, Hilly.
He's a friend of mine.

1027
01:25:42,768 --> 01:25:45,830
- Hello.
- Hi.

1028
01:25:45,830 --> 01:25:48,308
- So this is Mr. Big.
- That's the man.

1029
01:25:49,245 --> 01:25:51,110
You ain't sayin' shit now, Mr. Big.

1030
01:25:51,110 --> 01:25:54,877
I must admit that I'm slightly
at a loss for words.

1031
01:25:54,877 --> 01:25:57,544
But on the other hand,
I should warn you...

1032
01:25:57,544 --> 01:25:59,451
that you are a killer...

1033
01:25:59,451 --> 01:26:02,491
and you are wanted by the police
in every state...

1034
01:26:02,491 --> 01:26:06,392
and I recommend that
you, uh, be careful.

1035
01:26:07,129 --> 01:26:10,758
You're the killer who's wanted
by the police in every state.

1036
01:26:11,967 --> 01:26:15,562
That man you had shot wasn't a vitamin
salesman. He was a federal agent.

1037
01:26:15,562 --> 01:26:18,607
They've been after you
for two years.

1038
01:26:18,607 --> 01:26:22,734
Ever since that plane crash
in Cologne, Germany...

1039
01:26:22,734 --> 01:26:26,076
when you caused a hundred people
to die, just to cover up your link...

1040
01:26:26,076 --> 01:26:28,843
with the scandal
at the Metropolitan Gallery.

1041
01:26:28,843 --> 01:26:32,375
So why don't we get them
the proof that they wanted?

1042
01:26:33,454 --> 01:26:36,184
Let's go and get
the Rembrandt letters.

1043
01:26:43,731 --> 01:26:45,255
Get up.

1044
01:26:46,234 --> 01:26:48,031
If you insist.

1045
01:27:01,582 --> 01:27:03,345
- Get up, Whiney!
- Just do what he says.

1046
01:27:07,387 --> 01:27:09,378
Get the letters, Hilly.

1047
01:27:09,378 --> 01:27:11,253
Mr. Caldwell...

1048
01:27:11,253 --> 01:27:13,850
I take it that you are
a reasonable man and that,...

1049
01:27:13,850 --> 01:27:17,761
like all men, you place
a reasonable value on your life.

1050
01:27:17,761 --> 01:27:19,321
Are you trying to bribe me?

1051
01:27:19,321 --> 01:27:23,165
No. I'm merely pointing out
that life is short...

1052
01:27:23,165 --> 01:27:26,934
and the smart man
hedges his bets.

1053
01:27:26,934 --> 01:27:29,201
You can't protect bets.

1054
01:27:29,201 --> 01:27:31,402
If there's one thing
I have learned from this trip...

1055
01:27:31,402 --> 01:27:34,537
it's that you play the game
and take what you get.

1056
01:27:34,537 --> 01:27:37,208
- I found them!
- Come here, Hilly.

1057
01:27:37,950 --> 01:27:39,110
Get the girl.!

1058
01:27:53,966 --> 01:27:56,560
What do you think this is?
A western?

1059
01:28:00,239 --> 01:28:02,901
- What are you doing?
- I'm trying to save our asses!

1060
01:28:02,901 --> 01:28:06,307
- I'm not jumping!
- There's a bridge coming up. Get ready!

1061
01:28:06,307 --> 01:28:09,609
Goddamn it, I'm not jumping!
I left this train twice already!

1062
01:28:09,609 --> 01:28:12,582
- Get ready.!
- I'm not jumping!

1063
01:28:12,582 --> 01:28:15,142
Here it comes! Go!

1064
01:28:18,757 --> 01:28:20,349
Son of a bitch!

1065
01:28:24,596 --> 01:28:26,086
Shit!

1066
01:28:27,399 --> 01:28:29,230
Not again!

1067
01:28:47,484 --> 01:28:49,247
What are we gonna do now?

1068
01:28:49,247 --> 01:28:52,153
All right.!
Hold it right there.!

1069
01:28:55,993 --> 01:28:57,551
Shit.

1070
01:29:26,923 --> 01:29:30,154
I just talked to Chaney. He'll have
the helicopter ready in Rockdale.

1071
01:29:30,154 --> 01:29:32,217
Just about five minutes from the station.

1072
01:29:33,229 --> 01:29:34,753
We'll be there in 46 minutes.

1073
01:29:34,753 --> 01:29:39,734
Is there any way of stopping
this train between here and there?

1074
01:29:39,734 --> 01:29:42,669
Aside from the engine, there's
an emergency brake in each car.

1075
01:29:43,639 --> 01:29:46,540
- Disconnect them.
- Okay. All of them?

1076
01:29:46,540 --> 01:29:49,076
Yes, all of them.
And take her with you.

1077
01:29:50,178 --> 01:29:51,543
Come on.

1078
01:30:17,105 --> 01:30:19,266
They're yours.

1079
01:30:19,266 --> 01:30:21,809
- You George Caldwell?
- Will you please...

1080
01:30:21,809 --> 01:30:24,640
Would you just tell me...
Goddamn it!

1081
01:30:24,640 --> 01:30:27,681
Would you please tell me what the hell
we're doing here and what you want from me!

1082
01:30:27,681 --> 01:30:30,046
- You are George Caldwell?
- Yes, I'm George Caldwell.

1083
01:30:30,046 --> 01:30:33,280
- I want some information from you, and fast.
- I did not kill Sweet.

1084
01:30:33,280 --> 01:30:35,254
We know that. And if you weren't
so dumb,...

1085
01:30:35,254 --> 01:30:38,416
you would've realized that we planted
that news story for your own protection.

1086
01:30:38,416 --> 01:30:42,428
I've had men posted in every town
since Dodge City trying to pick you up...

1087
01:30:42,428 --> 01:30:44,623
while you're gallivanting around
the countryside wasting time.

1088
01:30:44,623 --> 01:30:48,634
- I didn't know they were federal agents!
- Well, let's see what you do know.

1089
01:30:51,305 --> 01:30:52,932
Here.

1090
01:30:52,932 --> 01:30:56,306
- How many men has Devereau got on the train?
- Two.

1091
01:30:56,306 --> 01:30:59,504
- What's his plan after they get to Chicago?
- He's not going to Chicago.

1092
01:30:59,504 --> 01:31:01,672
He's getting off at Rockdale.

1093
01:31:02,649 --> 01:31:04,810
I was afraid of that.
Okay.

1094
01:31:07,052 --> 01:31:09,543
Matthews, over here!

1095
01:31:11,056 --> 01:31:13,684
We're gonna stop the train
before Rockdale.

1096
01:31:13,684 --> 01:31:17,092
Closest is...
the Harris Mill Junction.

1097
01:31:17,092 --> 01:31:21,190
Contact the railroad. Tell them to make
out like it's a routine emergency inspection.

1098
01:31:21,190 --> 01:31:24,100
Have Bronsky bring his men
up in choppers from the south..

1099
01:31:24,100 --> 01:31:26,866
Get all the passengers off the train,
and I don't want any slip-ups.

1100
01:31:26,866 --> 01:31:29,840
We'll be there as soon as we can.
Caldwell, you come with us.

1101
01:31:29,840 --> 01:31:31,739
Steward, what do you want to do?

1102
01:31:31,739 --> 01:31:35,007
This has been a nerve-shattering
experience. I'd like to go home.

1103
01:31:35,814 --> 01:31:37,441
Take him anywhere he wants.

1104
01:31:37,441 --> 01:31:39,949
Okay, men, grab your rifles.
Let's move it.!

1105
01:31:39,949 --> 01:31:43,044
Caldwell, your shells.

1106
01:31:43,788 --> 01:31:44,508
Let's go.!

1107
01:31:45,957 --> 01:31:49,654
- What does he think I'm gonna do with this?
- Blow the tires out on the train.

1108
01:31:50,428 --> 01:31:51,690
Thanks for everything.

1109
01:31:54,032 --> 01:31:55,431
My pleasure.

1110
01:31:56,434 --> 01:31:58,732
Goddamn it.!
Caldwell, get out here.!

1111
01:31:58,732 --> 01:32:02,261
If there's ever anything
that you need...

1112
01:32:06,010 --> 01:32:07,340
don't call me.

1113
01:32:10,080 --> 01:32:12,207
Don't let 'em get you killed.

1114
01:32:16,119 --> 01:32:19,213
Take it easy, killer.
Stay loose.

1115
01:32:35,172 --> 01:32:37,333
Where'd you like to go, fella?

1116
01:32:37,333 --> 01:32:38,738
Well..

1117
01:32:41,210 --> 01:32:43,405
I left myJag in Kansas City.

1118
01:32:58,027 --> 01:33:00,257
I don't know, Frank,
but that's what they said.

1119
01:33:00,257 --> 01:33:02,524
Everybody off
at the Harris Mill Junction.

1120
01:33:02,524 --> 01:33:06,694
Everybody off?
Okay, I'll tell my crew.

1121
01:33:27,022 --> 01:33:31,254
- Why are they stoppin' the train?
-I don't know, sir. Tryin' to get some security check here.

1122
01:33:31,254 --> 01:33:33,521
That's the damnedest thing
I ever heard!

1123
01:33:33,521 --> 01:33:36,462
- They want us to get off the train?
- Yeah.

1124
01:33:37,933 --> 01:33:40,299
- Hey, there's the police!
- Watch your step. Watch your step.

1125
01:33:40,299 --> 01:33:42,666
- Well, I'll be...
- Come on, get back!

1126
01:33:42,666 --> 01:33:45,672
You guys are just totally uncontrollable.
You know that?

1127
01:33:56,050 --> 01:33:57,608
- The police are here.
- What?

1128
01:33:57,608 --> 01:34:00,279
The porters are askin' everyone
to get off the train.

1129
01:34:02,389 --> 01:34:04,084
Are they?

1130
01:34:06,860 --> 01:34:10,023
Keep moving towards the clearing, please.

1131
01:34:12,132 --> 01:34:16,228
This is a routine investigation.
None of you is in danger.

1132
01:34:17,805 --> 01:34:21,502
Please cooperate with us so we can
complete our investigation quickly...

1133
01:34:21,502 --> 01:34:24,703
and get you back aboard
and on your way.

1134
01:34:28,401 --> 01:34:29,702
Please keep moving...

1135
01:34:37,323 --> 01:34:38,847
Excuse me.

1136
01:34:41,561 --> 01:34:43,426
Yeah, excuse me.

1137
01:34:47,634 --> 01:34:51,070
- Everybody off, please, Mr. Devereau.
- Yes. What's happening here, Conductor?

1138
01:34:51,070 --> 01:34:54,163
We're not sure. We got a call from
the police wanting everyone evacuated.

1139
01:34:54,163 --> 01:34:56,902
- Maybe it's a bomb scare.
- A bomb scare?

1140
01:34:56,902 --> 01:34:59,705
- Then we'd better get off.
- I certainly am.

1141
01:35:37,615 --> 01:35:39,515
Stay with her.

1142
01:35:39,515 --> 01:35:43,178
Cover us from the window. We're gonna
start the engine and take this thing to Rockdale.

1143
01:35:43,178 --> 01:35:47,748
Hey, what are you doin'? Everybody's gone.
What are you doin' with those rifles?

1144
01:35:52,063 --> 01:35:54,122
You bastards!

1145
01:35:56,967 --> 01:35:59,731
Everyone's off, Chief,
except our boy.

1146
01:36:01,472 --> 01:36:03,099
Hold it right there, Devereau!

1147
01:36:54,456 --> 01:36:56,253
- Shit!
- Take it easy, killer.

1148
01:36:56,253 --> 01:36:58,486
What are you doing here?

1149
01:36:59,762 --> 01:37:01,923
What's going on?
Who's in charge here?

